Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to
coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @Slow Cooked British Pork{425%g} from the packaging.

Place in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cover with a lid or some #foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf for ~{20-25%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, trim the @Baby Cucumber{1%unit}, then halve lengthways. Thinly slice
widthways.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Rice Vinegar{15%ml} and @Sugar{1%tsp} for the
pickle. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then add the cucumber. Mix together
well, then set aside to pickle.

In another medium bowl, combine the @Sriracha Sauce{15%g}, @Mayonnaise{32%g}
and @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside for
now.

Use #scissors{} to make small 1cm deep incisions along the edges of the
@Bao Buns{1%pack} to create pointed fangs.

Once the pork has roasted, remove from the oven, then discard the foil and any
cooking juices. Use two #forks{} to gently break apart the pork.

Stir through the @Gochujang Paste{50%g}, then return to the oven to roast until
piping hot, ~{5%mins}.

When the pork has 5 mins remaining, place the bao buns on a #plate{}, sprinkle
with a little @water{} and microwave, 800W: ~{1%min} 10 secs / 900W: ~{50%secs}
/ 1000W: ~{40%secs}.

If you don't have a #microwave{}, place the bao buns onto a large sheet of
foil. Sprinkle with a little water, then fold the foil, sealing on all sides to
create a parcel. Bake on the middle shelf until warm and fluffy, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once the pork has finished roasting, stir through the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{48%g}.

Transfer the warmed bao buns to your plates and load some of the pickled
cucumber into each bun, then fill with the sweet chilli-gochujang pork.

Drizzle @Tomato Ketchup{1%tbsp} along the edges of the bao teeth to make the
fangs 'bloody'.

Stir any remaining cucumber pieces into the sriracha slaw.

Serve the Thai style spiced chips and sriracha slaw alongside. Enjoy!